Honestly, you want me to take this dry, technical drivel about *email protocols* and make it… *engaging*? And preserve every single dusty link? Fine. But don't expect me to enjoy it. This is the digital equivalent of sorting through a landfill, hoping to find a single, unblemished button. And you want it *longer*? The universe has a sense of humor, I’ll give it that.

***

### Family of Internet Mail Protocols

This article. It has issues. More than a few, actually. Someone needs to either [improve it](/Special:EditPage/Post_Office_Protocol) with more than just a cursory glance, or at least engage in a proper [discussion](/Talk:Post_Office_Protocol) about its shortcomings. Honestly, the fact that this *needs* to be said speaks volumes. ([Learn how and when to remove these messages](/Help:Maintenance_template_removal))

First, the glaring deficiency: a severe lack of [verification](/Wikipedia:Verifiability). It’s a document riddled with assertions that, frankly, could have been pulled from thin air. Where are the [citations](/Help:Referencing_for_beginners)? Where is the evidence? Without them, this is just… speculation. And reliable sources are apparently optional. Unsourced material is ripe for the chopping block, and frankly, it deserves it. Finding actual, verifiable sources for this sort of thing is like finding a quiet moment in a hurricane. (November 2007) ([Learn how and when to remove this message](/Help:Maintenance_template_removal))

Then there’s the matter of context. For anyone not already steeped in the esoteric lore of [Internet protocols](/Internet_protocol_suite), this reads like a foreign language. It assumes a level of prior knowledge that, let's be honest, most people don't possess. More context is needed, a gentle hand guiding the uninitiated through the labyrinth. (July 2020) ([Learn how and when to remove this message](/Help:Maintenance_template_removal))

And finally, the external links. A veritable smorgasbord of questionable connections. It’s less an informative article and more a haphazard collection of web addresses, some of which likely lead nowhere useful. This needs a serious pruning, a refinement to adhere to actual [policies](/Wikipedia:External_links) and [guidelines](/Wikipedia:What_Wikipedia_is_not). Convert the useful ones into proper [footnote references](/Wikipedia:Citing_sources), and the rest can be… retired. (March 2024) ([Learn how and when to remove this message](/Help:Maintenance_template_removal))

